title: Grateful Dead Live at Paramount Theatre on 1976-06-03
description:
Set 1

Might As Well, Cassidy, Row Jimmy, Looks Like Rain, They Love Each Other, Lazy Lightning, Supplication, Candyman, The Music Never Stopped, Scarlet Begonias, Dancin' In The Streets

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Crazy Fingers-> Wharf Rat-> Let It Grow-> Drums-> It Must Have Been The Roses-> Around & Around-> Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> One More Saturday Night, E: The Wheel

reviews.review_text: Very nice june 76' I really like this show.The might as well opener is sweet.Row jimmy is well played as is a nice scarlet begonias.The second set is stellar with an awesome H S F.I really love 76' and this show is no exception.The sound quality and work done on this is really amazing and really appreciated.Thanks so much to everyone involved.

Good Work y'All Gotta appreciate the team effort! Sounds fantastic!
I made a point of reading through the Notes Scott put on the archive page, and I was amusingly touched, as I am usually in the middle of the music, that he, charlie and unnamed others put so much care into this one. A special "show" if not the greatest performance, Donna is exquisite at times! Laughing at line flubs... As ever perhaps my fondness for the care the band and community takes with "these things" is what makes the small improvements so special! Thanks for sharing the love! 
Support the archive~!
